args:
Harle discovers a royal secret regarding what
happened ten days after the seventh child was
born and joyfully relays it to Elisanne. This new
information fills her with sudden doubts about
the prince she so loyally serves.
I, Finlorda, do hereby agree to grant\nthe wish of the human, Aurelius.

On said terms is the agreement
between our nations so sworn.

—Aurelius
—Finlorda
Ha ha ha! Oh, but one DOES find history\nin the most unexpected places.
I never thought to stumble upon such\nfascinating things in this, of all places.

Someone clearly tried to seal them away
from prying eyes—but alas and alack,
the former king's untimely passing
has weakened such protections.
Now truth will see the light,\nand chaos will follow after.
Ah, but the beginning of such times\ncan be so jolly indeed!
What WILL the vassals of that traitorous\nprince think when they learn of this?\nOoo, my excitement is palpable!
There! That is the church that\nrequested our aid!
This church is a known conservative\nstronghold. Are we safe to assume the\nperditionists are behind the attack?
None can say—communications were\nlost before they could do more than\nbeg us to help with all speed.
Regardless of what awaits us,\nour mission does not waiver.
We are here to save as many lives\nas possible—and we shall.

Hildegarde, lead the fleeing believers to
safety and tend to the injured as needed.
Julietta, circle around and cover the back.
I shall strike from the fore. ...Go!
May Ilia's blessing be with you.
This was no work of perditionists;\nit was the Empire!
The perditionists and Empire both worship\nthe Other, a stance to which conservatives\nare most strongly opposed.
It seems the Empire has turned their\nsights on the conservatives—likely for\ntheir refusal to worship the Other.
You are not wrong, my dear Paladyn.\nBut my main reason for coming here\ntoday is SO much more thrilling!
Ah, what a joy it is to see you again.
What are you doing here, wretch?!
Why, I've come to see you, of course!
And what better place to meet a Paladyn\nthan in the Goddess's stomping ground?
So I prepared this stage, chased away\nany who might interfere...and waited.
Are you saying you attacked this church\nmerely to draw me here?
I have something I would like you to see.

It is a secret regarding one you care about
as much as—if not more than—even Ilia.
It is about your dear, precious prince.
You must be a LITTLE interested, mmm?
I care naught about anything\nyou might have to say!
Ah, but you should care! Here, take a look.\nI recently found both this document and\nbook in a hidden room at the palace.
They contain a secret about the seventh\nprince that the former king struggled\nEVER so hard to keep hidden.

A seventh and eighth child have
been born to King Aurelius.
The seventh is named
{player_name}
and the eighth is named Zethia.
However, ten days following the birth\nof the seventh child...
Oh? And does the signature at the end\nnot at all sway you? I found it terrifically\ncompelling, myself.
It does appear to be King Aurelius's\nsignature and seal, but... No. No!\nI still won't believe it!
So you intend to turn a blind eye?\nWalk away whistling a merry tune\nand forget you ever saw it?
Is this how Paladyns and the Church\nbehave in the face of inconvenient truths?

Oh, how shaken you look! How pitiable!
Ah, but this HAS been fun, hasn't it?
Alas, I am needed elsewhere now.
Busy busy, that's me. Well, toodle-oo!
Why? So you might burn them and\nrelegate history to the ash heap?
I cannot allow that, my dear Paladyn.\nI need to watch you struggle, you see.\nI need to watch you SUFFER.
Yes, well, as I said before, ＂Toodle-oo.＂\n...Do take care of this one, won't you?
...Of course. Why would I not be?
You've been lost in thought since our\nreturn. Did something happen back there?
I'm...just a little tired, is all.\nI think I shall retire to my room.
Hey, Elly! Could I have a—
I'm sorry! Please leave me be!
(Could it be true? Could it REALLY?)
(I wish to deny it with all that I am,\nand yet, it was the royal family's seal.)
(But if what I saw there is true,\nit means my beloved prince is...)
